data folder contains mongodb collections
Main web application in app.js
Main angularjs stuff in controller.js
Packages.json contains the nmp (node package manager) config files for installing dependencies etc.
install nodejs. run npm and install express globally (npm install -g express).
install mongodb and run 
mkdir /pathto/cloned_repository/data [make a directory data]
mongod --dbpath path/to/cloned_repository/data
node app.js [fire up our web server using node]
And the site should run locally, Will take down the code after you've pulled, some major major changes need to be reworked
